# .trivyignore
#
# CVEs that have been reviewed and accepted as unfixable or false-positive
# for the AchaeanFleet container images.
#
# Format: each entry MUST be preceded by a 6-field structured comment block
# per SECURITY.md "CVE Suppression Policy" / "Required entry format":
#
#   # <CVE-ID>
#   # Category: OS | npm | python | other
#   # Rationale: <why it cannot be fixed here>
#   # Exploitability: <none | low | medium | ...> — justification
#   # Expires: YYYY-MM-DD  (max 90 days from approval; re-review before)
#   # Reviewer: @<github-handle>  PR #<number>
#   <CVE-ID>
#
# Reference: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore

# secret-0-generic-api-key
# Category: other
# Rationale: false-positive secret detections for placeholder values in .env.example; these are documentation examples, not real credentials.
# Exploitability: none — values are documented placeholder strings, never used at runtime.
# Expires: 2026-08-14
# Reviewer: @mvillmow  PR #TBD
secret-0-generic-api-key

